      <scopecontent id="aspace_e340172fd38cdbe6f3569a75afb1fa03">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Scanned copies (created in January 2014 and December 2016) of the constitution, 1832, of the Russell Trust Association; contract and architectural plan, 1866; and reminsciences of members, 1884.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_b6945f1c73de73496a264754ae84e70d">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Russell Trust Association is the trade name for the undergraduate senior society, Skull and Bones.  The Russell Trust Association was incorporated in 1856 by founding president of Johns Hopkins University, Daniel Coit Gilman.  The Russell Trust Association manages the finances of Skull and Bones, which goes towards the upkeep of its properties, associated taxes, and other considerations.</p>
      </bioghist>
